reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Perfect for my laptop and papers, stylish and sturdy, can be carried by shoulder strap or handles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing!! NO BAD SMELL—ignore the bad reviews!
reviews.reviewText: Amazing—great buy!! Love this bag for work and general outings!I was slightly skeptical to get this bc of some of the negative reviews about a “fishy smell”; that there’s no padding for the outer side of the laptop section; and that the bag falls over. ALL of those complaint-reviews seem like an exaggeration to me.I got this bag in Jan 2021 and there is absolutely NO BAD SMELL to this bag at all!! I was fully prepared to have to air this out like people mentioned, but this arrived and is completely normal with zero smell. I put it up to my face to smell it and stuck my nose inside the pockets, and it’s exactly like any normal bag you would buy at a store... I have no idea where people are getting that there’s a smell.As far as the padding issue goes—my laptop actually fit perfectly in the “iPad” section so that it was fully padded on both sides. I also have an even bigger laptop that fits here as well (as long as I place it slightly diagonal). Putting my laptop in the “iPad” section also means I don’t have the issue of the bag falling over like some reviews mentioned. I think people forget to consider the measurements before buying things like this, and that may be the problem here.Overall this is an amazing bag!! I took a photo in natural light to see it better, but the material is durable, the color is true to the description (and LOVE the deep green!), and it holds a ton of stuff. It is also lightweight, but doesn’t feel or look cheap to me. I will also note that the inside of the crossbody strap (removable) is made of a rope material (see pic), which makes it more comfortable on your shoulder than the solid leather on the outside of the strap. The photos show the metal parts as silver, but I love that it’s gold on the green bag! (I can’t speak to the other colors if they have gold or silver pieces.) There are also little pegs on the bottom to keep the bag from getting dirty or damaged. Love all these features!This is a fantastic laptop tote for this price and I highly recommend it!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The bag is a nice size, but look a little plasticky/cheap. It's fine for a work or travel bag. The main thing I wanted is a bag that zips so I can stick it under and airplane seat without worrying about things falling out. There are a few inner pockets, but I put my own purse organizer inside for an easier time switching between bags. I like the adjustable shoulder strap that attaches on the sides, but the short straps attaching with buckles are very annoying because they don't fold down. They were easy to remove, but now I just have empty buckles. Overall, it does what I need but isn't exactly stylish.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Such a nice bag!
reviews.reviewText: I was so surprised when the bag arrived. It was better than I ever could’ve expected. It looks high-quality professional, and looks so nice. It’s lightweight, there’s lots of room, but it’s not too big perfect for work. The price was so good I can get two different colors!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful and Sturdy
reviews.reviewText: I bought this bag about 5 years ago, and have used it almost daily since, including about a dozen times when traveling. The capacity is excellent - I carry my laptop, iPad, chargers, phone, files and paperwork, and miscellaneous smaller items easily. In fact, I can cram more into it than I can easily carry due to weight, so I have to remind myself of that. After five years, nary a rip or fray or popped stitch. It doesn’t scuff, the straps are intact and it doesn’t pick up dirt or grime. Fortunately, it’s pretty as well, or I’d be tired of looking at it by now. Definitely a purchase I’d recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Work Bag!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this wanting to replace the work backpack I had been using for something more sophisticated. For the price, the quality is impressive. It fits my 14” laptop, tablet, water bottle and more. The multiple pockets help keep it organized. I really enjoy the Velcro strap that holds in your laptop, making it feel so much more secure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars A little too stiff
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to use as a laptop bag plus some binders and the leather was just too stiff. It was a struggle to try to keep it open to shove things inside.Great looking bag and if you only want to throw your laptop and a few things in it's great! But I need something softer and easily opens wider especially if I want to just throw things in and run out of the conference room.
